	   <tr><td colspan=2>I play a lvl 40 Cleric. The HE clerics have the best starting wisdom, and it is OK to put your points into STR. You will need it. AC will be your savior. That means better armor. That means more weight. If it's not too late to start again, try putting points into str. I deleted the HE cleric at lvl 6 in favor of a DE. Which I also deleted at 6 due to the fact that he overweight. Both of these clerics, I put all thier starting points into wisdom. My last try, I dumped all the points I could into str and 5 into wisdom. Oh, I can hear ya out there (dumb dumb). But it makes a world of difference when you get that bronze armor on and you are not encumbered. At lvl 40 I have a base AC of 700 and my wisdom is 154. I have yet to be fired for having that low of a wisdom score. I take minimal damage when the critters decide to say "hi" and that will happen alot. <br><br>Thats my input. <br><br>Kad the Cleric of Innoruuk<br>Hate be my guide<br>The Nameless<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
