<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99495799374588></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99495799374588><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=99495799374588>RE: Is it really like this?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=99495799374588#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jul 12th 1:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>No, it does not have to be like this. I'm a LvL 20 HE cleric who solos most of the time. I prefer to solo, and do so well. Cleric spells and abilities are the most flexiable in the game, experiment with ALL of them, and you'll be shocked with what you can do. My best exp, loot, and fun comes from grouping with one or smoetimes two other players, but I don't "buff, heal med",I do most of the damage (DD) and keep the mobs under control (root, stun, fear, ect.). The problem so many players have being clerice is that they think like warriors, stop taking steriods and use your noodle. One of my alts is a Barb War, who is much better at melee, but is no better solo and spends as much time healing as my cleric does medding. Play wise, isn't that what clerics are know for, wisdom? Know your zone, mobs, drops, quest (a lot, better EXP than mobs), and have a plan. I do group, mostly at guild events, but guess what? I don't "buff, heal, med". What I do is control the mob (and player) traffic with my spells, serve as the communications center (directing the tanks) and other casters, turn and burn with my DD's (especialy against undead), heal as needed (should not be often if mobs are managed and plyers work as an organized team), and melee when the sh*t does hit the fan. Guys controling traffic is what casters do best in groups, OMG not just healers! you do it right and healing will rarely be cast, also doing it right conserves mana and health. It costs less to control the mobs than heal the taks when you don't(mana that is). This method allows for less down time for all, more exp, more loot, and more fun. <br><br>As far as the loot issue, yes I run into that, one reason I don't like to group much. My answer is simple, no loot, no heal. I warn them and then go offensive, only healing myself. When asked for a heal, I say where's my loot from the last train, when I saved your butt? Give me my sare and I'll heal you. If this doesn't make the point I warn again and leave when most needed. <br><br>Don't take anyone's crap, ever when it comes to loot. <br><br>Well that's just my two cents.<br><br>Eanamdar Moonshadow<br>Priest of Tunare<br>20th Circle of Wisdom<br><br>PS I have created a plan to reach lvl 30 that is 70% solo play. Boys, it can be done.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
