<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99477527813815></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99477527813815><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=99477527813815>RE: General</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=99477527813815#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 10th 10:27 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Thanks for the compliment :-)<br><br>I've already taken up a lot of space on this message board, but I notice a lot of posts have been added recently with which I cannot agree.<br><br>Loot:&nbsp;&nbsp;I know it hurts when the other ppl loot all the time... Cleric is a thankless and unrewarding job right up until level 39, when you learn to exp rez.  My advice is just to accept this.  It is perfectly possible to be a cleric wearing patchwork armour until this level.<br><br>At level 39, spend some time running around exp rezzing people for donations.  Remember the people who treat you poorly, and remember the people who treat you well... your bank balance will rocket upwards.<br><br>At level 49, with 90% exp rez, your bank balance takes another jump.  This is good, because you will need to spend literally thousands of platinum to buy Peridots.  These are absolutely essential in Sebilis.  Nevertheless, if you find yourself running out of cash, simply devote a couple of evenings to exp rezzing.<br><br>It may seem hard to believe when you're level 30, but you have chosen one of the highest-paid classes in the game /grin.<br><br>AC vs. Aggro control:  High AC is important at low levels, less important at high levels, because at high level aggro control becomes so important.  By the end game you will have lower AC than a tank and you will be more vulnerable.  YOU WILL learn to control your aggro eventually.  Basically the answer to aggro control is to group with a competent enchanter and some competent tanks, to let those people manage the mob's hate list rather than trying to manage it yourself, and to help them to do this by not unnecessarily annoying the mob.  Celestial Healing is a useful spell for this purpose, because it has a low taunt value for the amount of healing that it does... also you will need to learn when to sit down (which causes aggro), when to root, and when to use DA/DB.<br><br>People persist in asking where is the best place to gain levels... the answer is, wherever you can get into a good group.  If you are in the fortunate position of having the choice of several good groups, then Kunark has the fastest exp - but more important to get in a good group and build relationships with people you trust.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
